# Finding 053
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Identical `vitest.config.mjs` across client-element packages
- File + line(s): `packages/chat/chat-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/users/members-admin-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/users/profile-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/observability/console-errors-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/billing/billing-commerce-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/billing/billing-console-admin-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/billing/billing-plan-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/ai-agent/assistant-transcript-explorer-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`, `packages/ai-agent/assistant-client-element/vitest.config.mjs:1-10`
- Why it can drift/fail: Identical test configuration is copy-pasted into every client-element package. Any change in test setup must be propagated manually or these packages will drift.
- Concrete impact: Inconsistent test behavior between client-element packages, especially if environment or include patterns change.
- Exact remediation: Move to a shared `vitest` config (e.g., `@jskit-ai/config-vitest` or a shared `vitest.config.base.mjs`) and import it from each package.

## Resolution
- Justification: Client-side templates are actively being rewritten; per instruction, client-element changes are deferred to avoid conflicts. This is a low-severity duplication and safe to postpone.
- Revisit signal: Once client templates stabilize and there is a greenlight to touch client-element packages, consolidate the vitest config into a shared base and update the packages accordingly.
